- title "Software principles and practices to extreme levels"

%article.promo
  .info
    = image_tag('dalibor.nasevic.jpg', :alt => 'Dalibor Nasevic', :title => 'Dalibor Nasevic')
  .description
    %h2.hidden About

    %p <strong>Dalibor Nasevic</strong> is a <strong>Software Professional</strong> with passion for building successful web products and teams with strong desire to win.

    %p He is an <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=mk.popravi.mobile&hl=en" target="_blank">award-winning</a> Android developer and experienced <a href="https://github.com/dalibor" target="_blank">Ruby on Rails</a> developer working on numerous projects <a href="http://www.workingwithrails.com/person/13391-dalibor-nasevic" target="_blank">since 2007</a>.

    %p He is co-founder and organizer of <a href="http://ruby.mk" target="_blank">MKRUG</a> (Macedonian Ruby Users Group) and active member of <a href="/posts/31-global-day-of-coderetreat-in-skopje-macedonia">software craftsmanship</a> movement. He has given <a href="http://b10g.spodeli.org/search/label/ruby.mk" target="_blank">technical</a> presentations on web and mobile technologies.

    %p He has experience in product design and has co-founded few startups including: <a href="http://givebrand.com" target="_blank">givebrand.com</a> and <a href="http://popravi.mk" target="_blank">popravi.mk</a>. He has also experience implementing methodologies with Agile practices (Scrum, Kanban, XP) and mentoring developers in local and distributed teams.

    %p He has received B.Sc. in "Computer Engineering, Computer Science and Automatics" from <a href="http://www.feit.ukim.edu.mk/" target="_blank">FEIT</a> (Faculty of Electrical Engineering and Information Technologies) in Skopje.

    %p Currently he is working for <a href="http://www.siyelo.com/" target="_blank">Siyelo</a> - web application development consultancy with distributed teams in Cape Town and Skopje.

